    <!-- #7 Screaming Frog -->
    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-7" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#7 · FREE (500 URLS) · TECHNICAL AUDIT</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Screaming Frog — Best free technical SEO audit tool</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For any website that wants to find broken links, duplicate content, and missing metadata at paid-tool quality.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Screaming Frog's SEO Spider is the industry standard for technical audits, and the free version handles up to 500 URLs — enough for most small business websites. It finds broken links, missing meta descriptions, duplicate content, redirect chains, missing H1s, and indexability problems. The output matches paid crawlers in depth. Most local business sites have under 200 pages, so the 500-URL cap rarely binds. Desktop-only and no crawl-save on free are the real friction points.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Industry-standard technical audit quality — on par with paid tools</h4><p>The same crawler agencies use. At 500 URLs, the output is identical to the paid version — only the scale differs.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Catches broken links, duplicate content, redirect chains, missing H1s</h4><p>Finds the technical issues most responsible for ranking suppression — and gives you exact page URLs to fix.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>500-URL limit covers most small business sites completely</h4><p>The average local business website has 50-200 pages. The free limit is rarely the constraint it sounds like.</p></div></li>
