        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- #8 PageSpeed Insights -->
    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-8" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#8 · FREE · UNLIMITED · CORE WEB VITALS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Google PageSpeed Insights — Best free Core Web Vitals checker</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For businesses that want to measure Google's official ranking signals — LCP, INP, and CLS — for free.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">PageSpeed Insights scores your page's performance (0-100) for both mobile and desktop, combining lab data with real Chrome UX data. It measures LCP, INP, and CLS — the three Core Web Vitals Google uses as ranking signals. The real Chrome UX data shows how actual users experience your pages, not just how a test environment performs. One page at a time and score fluctuation between tests are the main friction points.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Measures Google's official ranking signals — LCP, INP, CLS</h4><p>No guessing what's hurting your Core Web Vitals score. Google tells you directly, for free.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Combines lab data with real Chrome UX user data</h4><p>Lab scores tell you what could be faster. Real user data tells you what is slower for actual visitors.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Separate mobile and desktop scoring</h4><p>Mobile scores almost always differ from desktop. Google weights mobile. Check both.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest limitation: one page at a time, scores fluctuate between runs</h4><p>No bulk page testing. A single page can show different scores on consecutive tests due to server variance. Run three times and average.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
